This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with the task of video deblurring. The use of attention mechanisms also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.MM) and deep learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a new dataset and uses it to evaluate the proposed method, which could place it in the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper also discusses the spatial and temporal dimensions of blur, which could make it relevant to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category.
